node.text:
Ok-working out your lats won't actually make your waist smaller, but it WILL give the illusion of a smaller waist! The more you widen the shoulders, chest and lats, the thinner your waist will appear.
.
These are two of my favorite workouts for lats/back on the FT-2 from @inspirefitnessofficial ! I have completely stopped going to the gym since getting the FT-2 and I'm not planning on going back anytime soon.
.
If you've got a little bit of room and it's within your budget, I highly recommend this machine. You'll never have to buy another piece of equipment again and you don't NEED a gym membership. 
.
Comment any workout questions here and I'll do my best to answer!
.
Link in bio to purchase the FT-2.
.
You can also see a bunch of free workouts on the Inspire Fitness App in the meantime :)

node.title: Workout your lats for a smaller waist??!

node.text:
Workout of the week with the FT-2 from @inspirefitnessofficial ! It still blows my mind how many different ways this can be used. I'm discovering new exercises almost daily.
.
If you've got a little bit of room and it's within your budget, I highly recommend this machine as it's been a written game-changer for me.
.
Comment any workout questions here and I'll do my best to answer!
.
You can also see a bunch of free workouts on the Inspire Fitness App in the meantime :)

node.text:
I've had this machine, the FT-2 from @inspirefitnessofficial for a couple months now and I'm still discovering new ways to use it. There are hundreds-if not thousands-of workout variations that can be done with this machine.
.
I'm going to start posting these weekly, be sure to comment any workout questions here and I'll do my best to answer!
.
You can also see a bunch of free workouts on the Inspire Fitness App in the meantime :)

node.text:
Just a little lonely Friday evening leg lift!
.
I've been using this contraption I built for over 6 months now and I'll honestly never go back to a traditional back/bar squat. I have had back problems since college and the slightest little tweak during traditional squats could put me out for WEEKS.
.
Zero injuries using this and I feel my legs are getting just as much work (or more) then the traditional back squat.
.
So if you have back problems, or are squatting heavy and getting tired of the bar digging into your traps (I'm not too macho to admit I hate this too lol) give these a try 💪🏼
